text.32: Taoiseach confirms that Ireland will go to Level 5 restrictions for six weeks from Wednesday night.
text.33:
The Taoiseach has described measures introduced in recent weeks as "Europe's strictest regime" and says they have been mildly successful in curbing the spread of the virus - but he says it has not been enough to reduce new case numbers.

"Broader action is now required," he says.
text.34:
Taoiseach says that taking a 'zero-Covid' approach is not possible given Ireland's geographical location and the NI border.

He also says that a 'herd immunity' approach is not possible because it would ignore the risk to vulnerable groups.
text.35:
The Taoiseach begins by saying that 2020 has been a difficult year, and that it's not over yet.

He asks everyone to take the threat of Covid-19 seriously.
